  <h2>Our commitment</h2>
  <p><strong>Gemini AMPM Ltd</strong> (company number 03437130) is committed to acting ethically and with integrity in all our business dealings. We have a zero-tolerance approach to modern slavery and human trafficking, both within our own business and across our supply chain.</p>
  <p>While our annual turnover is below the &pound;36m threshold at which a formal section 54 statement is mandatory under the Modern Slavery Act 2015, we publish this statement voluntarily to align with the expectations of our clients, framework partners and the public-sector procurement portals through which much of our work is awarded.</p>

  <h2>About our business</h2>
  <p>Gemini AMPM is a fire safety, security, ventilation, gas suppression, passive fire and life-safety contractor headquartered in Burgess Hill, West Sussex. We are an Employee Ownership Trust (EOT) and a wholly owned subsidiary of AMPM Group Limited. We employ directly-engaged engineers, supplemented by sub-contracted specialist labour where appropriate to scope and accreditation.</p>

  <h2>Our supply chain</h2>
  <p>Our supply chain comprises:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Direct manufacturers and product suppliers (UK and European, predominantly tier-1 brands listed on our <a href="/manufacturers/">manufacturers page</a>)</li>
    <li>Trade distributors and wholesalers</li>
    <li>Specialist sub-contractors carrying their own third-party accreditations</li>
    <li>Professional services providers (insurance, legal, accountancy, IT)</li>
  </ul>
  <p>The majority of our spend is with UK-incorporated suppliers and manufacturers, with secondary spend across European-headquartered manufacturers. We do not directly source labour or product from jurisdictions outside the UK or EU.</p>

  <h2>Risk assessment</h2>
  <p>We assess that the modern-slavery risk in our direct operations is <strong>low</strong>: we employ directly through PAYE under formal contracts with appropriate right-to-work checks, our supply chain is predominantly UK-based, and the materials we install are produced by tier-1 manufacturers operating under their own published modern-slavery commitments.</p>
  <p>The primary residual risk sits in our use of <strong>sub-contracted labour for peak workload</strong>, where the contractual chain can be longer. We mitigate this through:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Right-to-work documentation checks on every sub-contracted operative working on our sites</li>
    <li>Preference for sub-contractors who hold the same third-party accreditations as Gemini (BAFE, NSI Gold, FIRAS, CHAS, etc.) — accreditations that themselves require ethical-employment evidence</li>
    <li>Requirement that all sub-contractors confirm their own compliance with the Modern Slavery Act 2015 as part of their onboarding terms</li>
    <li>Inclusion of modern-slavery clauses in our standard sub-contract terms</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Policies and procedures</h2>
  <p>We maintain the following policies and procedures relevant to combating modern slavery:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Anti-slavery and human trafficking policy</li>
    <li>Recruitment and right-to-work-check procedures</li>
    <li>Sub-contractor onboarding due diligence</li>
    <li>Whistleblowing policy with confidential reporting route</li>
    <li>Procurement and supplier-management policy</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Training and awareness</h2>
  <p>Modern slavery awareness is included in our induction for new employees. Operational and procurement staff receive specific guidance on identifying potential indicators in the supply chain and on the reporting routes available.</p>

  <h2>Effectiveness</h2>
  <p>We have not identified any cases of modern slavery in our business or supply chain in the current or previous financial year. We will continue to monitor and report annually.</p>

  <h2>Reporting concerns</h2>
  <p>Any person with concerns about modern slavery in our business or supply chain can report them confidentially to <a href="mailto:info@geminiampm.co.uk">info@geminiampm.co.uk</a>. Concerns can also be reported to the UK Modern Slavery &amp; Exploitation Helpline on 08000 121 700.</p>

